OL,3,CHealth officials monitoring Welsh
OL,4,Cresidents linked with hantavirus
OL,5,Coutbreak
OL,7,FAccording to Public Health Wales, it
OL,8,Fis not spread through everyday social
OL,9,Fcontact like going to public spaces,
OL,10,Fshops, workplaces, or schools. In the
OL,11,F"rare" instances where a person has
OL,12,Fcaught the infection from another
OL,13,Fperson, they have had "close and
OL,14,Fprolonged contact" with the individual
OL,15,Fwho has been infected with hantavirus,
OL,16,Fthe organisation has said.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/8
